far, where you can turn a

00:04:21.829 --> 00:04:26.240
Gaussian distribution into
a uniform distribution.

00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:28.510
So you can take your Gaussian
distribution of random

00:04:28.510 --> 00:04:31.380
numbers, and you can flip it
around and give them all a

00:04:31.380 --> 00:04:33.770
uniform probability.

00:04:33.770 --> 00:04:36.350
Now, I don't want to do the
maths for you because that

00:04:36.350 --> 00:04:39.690
would be painful for everybody,
but it works.

00:04:39.690 --> 00:04:42.830
And so you can, then, generate a
uniform probability sequence

00:04:42.830 --> 00:04:43.740
of numbers.

00:04:43.740 --> 00:04:44.700
MALE SPEAKER: But we
